
[1]hideous

   HID'EOUS, a.

   1. Frightful to the sight; dreadful; shocking to the eye; applied to
   deformity; as a hideous monster; a hideous spectacle; hideous looks.

   2. Shocking to the ear; exciting terror; as a hideous noise.

   3. Detestable.
